        <h2>Probation, Prison & Post-Release: The Long Tail of Punishment</h2>
        <p>Once sentenced, Arizonans face a labyrinth of punitive supervision. Our <strong>Criminal Legal System Reform</strong> program revealed that technical probation violations—missing a meeting, failing a drug test—account for 35% of prison admissions. Private probation companies profit from monthly fees that push people deeper into debt. We champion probation term limits and presumption of early termination for compliance.</p>
        <p>Inside ADCRR facilities, the crisis is acute. Overcrowding exceeds design capacity while medical care delays result in preventable deaths. Solitary confinement operates without external monitoring. Our <strong>Independent Prison Oversight</strong> work confirms these failures. The <strong>ARTS in Prison & Think Motion</strong> program provides a lifeline, but cannot fix systemic abuse. We need the Ombudsman's Office fully funded and fiercely independent.</p>
        <p>Post-release barriers create permanent second-class citizenship. Arizona denies voting rights to over 200,000 residents with felony convictions. Occupational licensing boards reject applicants with records for most healthcare, education, and trades jobs. Our <strong>Core Civics & Advocacy Training</strong> helps returning citizens navigate these barriers while advocating for automatic rights restoration and "ban the box" expansion.</p>
